cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.PL, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving software quality through the use of static bug finders. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper leverages deep neural networks to train the bug finder. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a classification task to train the bug finder. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper proposes a novel interval-based propagation mechanism to improve the generalization of the neural network on larger graphs. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on security specifically, but rather on catching bugs in general.
